Love, Love, Love these gal pals. Having moved to a very rural area to be with my mom, as I promised my dad, I feel I actually have four new friends, at least when I miss all the friends I've made moving around the states, and unable to keep the longest, greatest friendship alive that I had due to after she married, she went ugly negative.  I so thought we had a bond since we were both only children, but she was very spoiled, whereas I didn't get spoiled till I moved away from my parents, but they taught me respect and the love of a family. Unfortunately, a week before my dad died of lung cancer, we were talking on the phone and she was mad at her mom for not taking her out to eat or shop and said she wished her mom was dead? I just cried and she just became so insensitive to anybody, even after two years and 3 times trying to get her head out of the rage inside of her, I had to give up on my best friend after so many years of happy, laughing till we cried, and the downs, it was too much for my soul to bare.  But at least I have my girlfriends when I watch these women and admire every little detail of the movies and shows, I wish they would make another movie.  I think these ladies are fabulous at any age and any time. It makes me want to at least visit, if not move to New York, but for now I get to watch them over and over again, thanks to Blu-Ray and everyone involved in making "Sex and the City" the unbelievably awesome shows and movies that will be a legend for all history and that women will love till the end of times.
